JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s rand retreated from its firmest level in almost three weeks on Tuesday as a firmer dollar and lingering political uncertainty cut short the previous week&#8217;s recovery.At 0640 GMT, the rand had slipped 0.53% to 13.3600 per dollar compared to a close of 13.2900 overnight in New York.The currency retreated from levels last seen on March 31 around 13.2600, ending a rally that saw the unit gain 4.5% as it recovered ground lost following the firing of the finance minister and two credit downgrades to junk. recovery by the dollar from five-month lows triggered by comments from US Treasury Secretary that the greenback was due to gain in the long term also drove the rand lower.Stocks are set to open lower at 0700 GMT, with the JSE securities exchange&#8217;s Top-40 futures index down 0.26%.In fixed income, the yield for the benchmark government bond due in 2026 fell 1 basis point to 8.815%.